The [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub Corporation]] '''X-30 "Lancer" target blast pistol''' was a lightweight and easy to use [[Sporting blaster/Legends|sporting blaster]]. The Lancer was one of the most popular sporting blasters on the market, specifically designed with competition shooters and hunters in mind; it was optimized for range, accuracy, and stopping power.

==Description==
Built to the [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub Corporation's]] exacting standards, the Lancer was a sleek, modern-looking [[Sporting blaster/Legends|sporting]] [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]] with a long [[Barrel/Legends|barrel]] and a weighted, finely-balanced [[Stock/Legends|stock]], designed for hunters and competition shooters. The Lancer was designed with a custom-formulated, highly volatile mix of [[Blaster gas/Legends|blaster gases]] and a supercharged [[Actuating module/Legends|actuating module]] to fire an intense, highly concentrated beam over longer ranges. Superior [[galven pattern]]s in the barrel reduced beam degradation and dispersal, which allowed the pistol to maintain effectiveness beyond other blaster pistols in its class.<ref name="EtU" />

==History==
[[File:Leia_endorpromo01.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Princess Leia with a Lancer pistol]]
Among the most popular models of sporting blaster, Lancer pistols were relatively common in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]], appealing to the need for a pistol with both power and light weight. Many [[pilot]]s of [[speeder]]s and atmospheric craft kept a Lancer in an easy-to-reach storage locker, and many [[starship]]s include them in their [[escape pod]]s and emergency kits for self-defense. They were also popular among [[scholar]]s and [[Scout/Legends|explorers]] for their reliability and easy handling, as well as big game hunters who enjoyed the challenge of pistol hunting.<ref name="EtU" />

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], both [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] and [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] personnel made use of the Lancer.<ref name="KennerAD">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (toy line)|pack=AT-ST Driver|link=VINtATSTDriver.asp}}</ref><ref name="KennerBP">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (toy line)|pack=B-wing Pilot|link=VINtBWingpilot.asp}}</ref> [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Netrem Pollard/Legends|Netrem Pollard]] wielded a Lancer pistol as the leader of [[Dagger Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Dagger Squadron]].<ref name="HasbroBW">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: The Legacy Collection|pack=Dagger Squadron B-wing Fighter|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/tlcvehBwing.asp}}</ref>
Later, during the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], the Alliance's [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] used the Lancer,<ref name="Chee">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?messageID=16047412#15881207|thread=The Essential Guides, second edition|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-11-03|time=10:35 AM}}</ref> as did many Rebel starfighter pilots,<ref name="KennerBP" /><ref name="KennerAP">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: The Power of the Force (1985 toy line)|pack=A-Wing Pilot|link=VINtAWingPilot.asp}}</ref> [[Imperial gunner/Legends|Imperial gunners]],<ref name="KennerIG">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: The Power of the Force (1985 toy line)|pack=Imperial Gunner|link=VINtImperialgunner.asp}}</ref> and [[All Terrain Scout Transport/Legends|AT-ST]] [[Vehicle Command Crewer#AT-ST pilots|drivers]] in that same conflict.<ref name="KennerAD" />

==Behind the scenes==
This pistol was first used by Princess Leia in {{Film|VI}}. It was created by modifying a Soviet-manufactured Margolin target pistol. The same model pistol was the basis for the longer-barreled [[Defender sporting blaster pistol/Legends|Defender sporting blaster pistol]] used by Leia in {{Film|IV}}.<ref name="SWI 59">{{InsiderCite|59|Set Piece|Set Piece: Rebel Alliance Briefing Room}}</ref>

